This paper presents a method for controlling the motion and contact forces of a floating-base robot, which is a common problem in robotics. The paper focuses on the optimization problem arising in multitask motion/force control frameworks, which is a core topic in robotics and falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the dynamics of the robot, which is related to system theory (cs.SY). The method presented in the paper involves optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulations carried out in the paper involve a humanoid robot, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves processing visual data. Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of the proposed controller, which is related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
